text: I've hard cast a Force before

Even in decks with blue I tend to run more black draw spells. Sure, there's Brainstorm for small draw, but generally I'd rather run Night's Whisper, Sign in Blood and Read the Bones over anything not named Brainstorm that blue has, and even one level up I'd rather run Ambition's Cost/Ancient Craving than anything blue has at that CMC not named Facot or Fiction. Are there cards I'm missing or underrating in blue that should be ran in those slots over the black ones?
Does Rhystic Study count?
Now we have Chart a Course. That's very good.
Wasn't really thinking permanents, but I'd run that alongside Arena
I think the thing you're missing is that blue has incendental draw as part of their spells
I also like Frantic Search, and the cards that let you draw three and then discard a land or an artifact or whatever
Chart is good, but the problem is it's not reliable on T2-3 to not have to discard. I'd rather have to pay 2 life and keep everything
Frantic Search is slightly different becuase it's so good in a reanimator deck.
Artificer's Epiphany is one I like.
It's fine but I'm not running it over the three black draws I mentioned.
I think it's a standard issue. Two life in a 20 mana format is a whole different thing than in a 40 life format

In a 20 losing no life and pitching 1 card or whatever is much more tempting than losing two. In a 40 mana format the life loss is so much less impactful that it makes the black draw cards better than intended compared it blue
You're right that 2 mana draw two is just really strong. I probably wouldn't run any single blue draw spells over the black ones.
But in blue, I like the ones I said, Compulsive Research, Thirst for Knowledge, and Tragic Lesson.

It's just one of those things that makes me feel like I'm missing something in a blue/black deck when I'm running Sign in blood. I feel like those spells should be blue, but nothing seems to quite measure up
I think what you're missing is recurrsion in deck dana
in decks where you want your yard filled with spells, I run the draw and discard as much as possible
but if you don't care about your yard all that much, the raw card draw is best
That might be it

It's not that I don't care necessarily, it's that it doesn't seem consistent enough. I could pay a little life and keep the cards, or I could pitch them and hope nobody has grave hate and hope I draw recursion. Feels like too many variables compared to just keeping everything.
it's a greedy view you're taking there too, not that it's wrong
the other real advantage of blue draw is the instant speed ones, where you can represent counters, and have the draw on the backup
Anyone have experience with Deathreap Ritual? In the right deck it looks better than Phyrena to me
